**Hello World in 10 Popular Programming Languages**

---

**1. Python**
```python
print("Hello, World!")
```

---

**2. Java**
```java
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
    }
}
```

---

**3. JavaScript**
```javascript
console.log("Hello, World!");
```

---

**4. C++**
```cpp
#include <iostream>
int main() {
    std::cout << "Hello, World!" << std::endl;
    return 0;
}
```

---

**5. C#**
```csharp
using System;
class HelloWorld {
    static void Main() {
        Console.WriteLine("Hello, World!");
    }
}
```

---

**6. Go**
```go
package main
import "fmt"
func main() {
    fmt.Println("Hello, World!")
}
```

---

**7. Ruby**
```ruby
puts "Hello, World!"
```

---

**8. PHP**
```php
<?php
echo "Hello, World!";
?>
```

---

**9. Swift**
```swift
print("Hello, World!")
```

---

**10. Kotlin**
```kotlin
fun main() {
    println("Hello, World!")
}
```
